cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this dataset or replication package, please cite as below."
title: "FHA Unified Database: Replication Package"
authors:
  - family-names: Gill
    given-names: Nicholas
    email: "nickgill@arizona.edu"
    affiliation: "J.D. Candidate, 2027, University of Arizona James E. Rogers College of Law"
type: dataset
date-released: 2026-04-01
url: "https://github.com/NickGillArizona/displacing-deference"
repository-code: "https://github.com/NickGillArizona/displacing-deference"
abstract: >-
  Replication package containing the FHA Unified Database (2,522 screened-in
  federal FHA opinions; 1,770 disability), LLM classification pipeline
  documentation, race-by-disability housing cost-burden cross-tabulations
  from ACS PUMS, HUD administrative-system analyses (CDBG, REAC/NSPIRE,
  POSH), and supplementary appendices. Supports two publications: an
  empirical article on composition effects in disability fair housing
  litigation and a companion doctrinal note on disability-centered AFFH.
keywords:
  - fair housing act
  - disability
  - AFFH
  - empirical legal studies
  - LLM classification
  - composition effect
  - housing cost burden
  - replication package
  - census pums
  - computational legal studies
